						<summary>

						<p>The record refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalladēva</hi> (i.e. <hi rend="bold">Sōmēśvara I</hi>) and is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka 969, Sarvajit, Chaitra, amāvāsyā, Sunday, solar eclipse (= A.D. 1047, March 29, Sunday).</hi> It registers a grant of land made by <hi rend="bold">Akkādēvī,</hi> while she was encamped at <hi rend="bold">Gōkāge,</hi> to the <hi rend="bold">Goṇadabeḍaṅgi-Jinālaya</hi> temple at <hi rend="bold">Vikramapura</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi> Arasibīḍi) and to Nāgasēna-Paṇḍita of the Hogari-gachchha, the Varasēna-gaṇa and the Mūla-saṅgha.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XVII, page 121).</p>						

						<p>In the readings given there the following emendations may be made:—</p>						

